title: so ~
body:
I’ve deleted everything, and this will be the 5th new post I’ll have on my blog.

I don’t really have a good explanation - just that it felt like it was time, and I didn’t really want to build up anything by giving a day or two’s warning. 

I truly appreciate everything writing on this blog has given me, and everything you guys have given me. I am a more confident writer, eons more than I was back in September 2017. It’s truly appreciated, I’ll always have a love for every fic and every reader on this blog.

Honestly, right now, I’m not aiming to delete the entirety of this blog - I like having a space to shit post about my love for Harry Styles, and I reblog so much, it wouldn’t really work on my main. I am considering sharing my main, as more of my writing will be on there (factoring in more of a personal writing style, but because I will always have my HS ‘persona’ in mind, there may be a blurb or two that’s reminiscent of the characters I’ve built on here).

love you guys :)

caption:
Wait, what? Of course he looks happy because he’s being forced to do what he doesn’t want to do? He looks happy but it’s obvious he doesn’t love the show?

What a reach, what twisting, what painful ignoring of reality to arrive at this conclusion. 

Go on, keep being supportive of what you believe to be Louis’s abuse. If that’s what you truly believe, I don’t know how justify this.

title: Spider ~ Harry Styles
body:
Summary: Your daughter has a spider in her room, Harry goes to help her out

Pairing; Dad!Harry x reader, Darcy

Warnings: None

Harry’s pov

I woke up by the screaming of my four year old daughter Darcy, I quickly got out of bed putting on some pyjama pants and rushed to her room. When I opened the door I saw her jumping on the bed.

“Darcy, Honey what are you doing?” “Daddy you have to save me there is a spider. You need to kill it before it eats me.” She screamed. “Cupcake, spiders can’t eat you and you need to be quite you’re going to wake up mommy.” I laughed.

“Daddy this isn’t funny.” “I’m sorry baby, where is the spider?” I asked in a serious tone now. “How would I know?” She shrugged. “Baby girl two seconds ago you were and now you’re telling me you don’t know were it is?”

“Well then the spider must be gone.” She shrugged again. “You know you really scared me little one.” I said sitting next to her on the bed. “I’m sorry daddy, but I do have a good way to make it up to you.” She smiled up at me. “Oh yeah?” “Yep, I was thinking I could sleep in yours and mommy’s bed so I can keep you both warm.” She said already making her way to our bedroom.

When she got there she climmed on the bed. She kicked down the comforter with her small feet and went to lay on top of y/n nuzzling in to her neck. I smiled to myself at the sight of my two girls and joined them in bed.
